	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Human and Half-Elf Druids start out at Surefall Glade, which is a bit NE of the city Qeynos.  The Glade is a quiet little place--there's no bank  and you'll have to journey to Qeynos for any vocational kits and armor beyond a shield.  There's a Druid guild and a Ranger guild.  You can buy your spells for the first few levels there, provision and occasionally find a starting weapon.  The caves behind the falls have bears which are friendly to Druids &amp; Rangers--stop by and feed them a fish or two.  The caves also have a few poachers who are definitely unfriendly, so don't drop your guard back there (i.e. go fishing, meditate, memorize spells) until you're higher level.  The exit to Qeynos Hills is through a long tunnel, so nightvision or a light source is good.  The hunting for new characters is rats, bats, snakes, decaying skeletons and gnoll pups in the Hills.  There are guards at the entrance, so you do have a safe place to retreat to.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
