	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The starting point for the Wood Elf Druid lies in the City of Kelethin.<BR>
Kelethin at first is a little bit confusing at first but after wandering around a bit<BR>
it becomes much more familar.  Greater Faydark is a great area to hunt because of the large<BR>
diversity of monsters there.  At levels 1-4 you'll most likely stay at the ruins near kelethin<BR>
killing decaying skeletons, bats, wasp drones, widow hatchlings, and orc pawns.  This forest is<BR>
home to the black wolf friend of Tunare and the Druidic order.  Kelethin contains a variety of<BR>
different shops to purchase armor and traveling gear such as backpacks and bags.  Weapons can be<BR>
found on most monsters in the forest so save your money for spells.  Spells are available in the Druid<BR>
and ranger guild within Kelethin, and those that cannot be found there can be found in the wizards guild<BR>
in Felwithe.  Once a Druid ascends to the 5th level and above his options for hunting open up a bit.  The <BR>
great thing about the greater faydark area is that there are many places to fight.  There are the bandit camps<BR>
the Orc camps, Crushbone area, and you can even venture to the ButcherBlock mountains for a bit of a change.<BR>
  
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
