	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				   Some Druids may well be confused about the talk of them getting the tracking skill at level 20 when they don't.  In fact all Druids DO get tracking at level 20, but for some reason the Surefall Glade trainers don't have it on their list.  If you started a druid at Surefall Glade, don't despair!  You can go to one of the other druid trainers at Riverdale or Feydywr and get trained in tracking at level 20.  (This bug (that surefall glade trainers don't train tracking) may be fixed in the future).<BR>
   It should be noted that half-elf druids do not have to start in Qeynos as previously noted, depending on the diety selected they are also able to start at the city of the Wood Elves.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
