	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I would just like to say that I think druids are by far the best non-mage spellcasters.  How many other classes can just walk around bears and wolves at low level and not even half to worry about being attacked?  How many other classes have the variety of spell effects? None.  I played a Warrior when I first started and got him to tenth level.  After spending hours healing, I thought I would try something else.  It was well worth it to me.  Now everytime I think about that warrior, I just cast a spell and remember why I switched.  Thanks for listening.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
